Document: ResourceSaver
Path: godot/classes/class_resourcesaver.rst
Summary: Provides static methods for saving resources to disk.

ResourceSaver is a singleton class that provides static methods for saving resources to disk. It allows you to save any Resource object to a file in a format that Godot can understand.

Inherits: Object

Methods:
save(resource: Resource, path: String, flags: int = 0) → Error
  Saves a Resource to the given path.
  The path must be a valid file path within the project.
  The flags argument can be used to specify how the resource should be saved.
  Possible flags:
  - ResourceSaver.FLAG_NONE (0): No special flags.
  - ResourceSaver.FLAG_REPLACE_SUBRESOURCES (1): Replace subresources with unique IDs.
  - ResourceSaver.FLAG_IGNORE_TYPE_MISMATCH (2): Ignore type mismatches when saving.
  - ResourceSaver.FLAG_COMPRESS (4): Compress the saved resource.
  - ResourceSaver.FLAG_RELATIVE_PATHS (8): Save paths as relative to the resource being saved.
  - ResourceSaver.FLAG_SHARED_FILES_AS_TEXT (16): Save shared files as text.
  - ResourceSaver.FLAG_EMBED_RESOURCES (32): Embed resources directly into the saved file.
  Returns an Error code indicating success or failure.

get_recognized_extensions() → Array[String]
  Returns an array of file extensions that ResourceSaver can recognize.

set_translate_ids(enable: bool)
  Sets whether to translate resource IDs to their original names when saving.
  This is useful for debugging and can make saved resources more readable.

is_translate_ids_enabled() → bool
  Returns whether translating resource IDs to their original names is enabled.

set_compress_local_files(enable: bool)
  Sets whether to compress local files when saving.
  This can reduce the file size of saved resources.

is_compress_local_files_enabled() → bool
  Returns whether compressing local files is enabled.

set_desktop_icon_save_path(path: String)
  Sets the path where desktop icons should be saved.
  This is only relevant when saving resources that can be used as desktop icons.

get_desktop_icon_save_path() → String
  Returns the path where desktop icons are saved.
